oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Charles & Alice Chapman House
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Edwin Best
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Greenback (Tenn.);
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Three of the Scott children in front of the Chapman's house. Clapboard siding. Wood shingles. Two chimneys. Two trees in front of house. The girl wears a dress. The two boys are in shorts and have suspenders. All three are barefoot.
